Both required outputs are in place: `transcript.json` (25 iterations, 68 hypotheses, 68 analyses, schema-validated) and `analysis_summary.txt` (150 lines).

**Top findings:**
- **PFS drivers (R²=0.97 with ~7 features):** feature_078 (age-like, +0.18 mo/unit, r=+0.85), feature_057 (3-level stage-like ordinal, −2.3 mo at level 2), feature_013 (PSA-like, log-coef −0.38), feature_051 (binary disease-burden flag, −0.52 mo), feature_009 (albumin-like, +0.48), feature_006 (−0.077), feature_109 & feature_039 (binary, each +0.15 mo).
- **Notable interactions:** age × feature_051 (negative, p<1e-46), stage × feature_051 (positive level-2 contrast, p≈4e-9), PSA × stage (p<1e-4), and feature_109 × feature_039 super-additive synergy (+1.42 mo when both vs ~+0.3 mo expected).
- **No demographic disparity:** race (feature_018) and insurance (feature_045) show no main effects on PFS, no interactions with clinical features, no differential clinical-feature prevalence, and no age-composition differences.
